The cardiothoracic from Baptist?

85
00:05:26,226 --> 00:05:28,388
Yeah. Isn't this week...

86
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:30,760
Yeah. Hey, get
Max down here now.

87
00:05:30,897 --> 00:05:31,921
Oh.

88
00:05:32,699 --> 00:05:34,659
Okay, as I fit you for
the radiation mask,

89
00:05:36,236 --> 00:05:39,001
remember you have
to keep absolutely still.

90
00:05:40,006 --> 00:05:42,532
I always found stillness to be a
highly overrated human ability.

91
00:05:42,609 --> 00:05:43,668
Consider it practice

92
00:05:44,377 --> 00:05:46,869
for when we aim high
energy external beam radiation

93
00:05:46,947 --> 00:05:48,882
at the cancer in your throat.

94
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:52,509
If you move then, you die.

95
00:05:52,786 --> 00:05:56,348
Has anyone ever told you you would
make a great James Bond villain?

96
00:05:56,623 --> 00:05:59,525
Uh, Max, you cannot move.

97
00:05:59,759 --> 00:06:00,783
Right.

98
00:06:01,595 --> 00:06:03,791
So, uh, come here often?

99
00:06:04,097 --> 00:06:07,033
That includes your
mouth. All of it? Because...

100
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:10,093
Do I have to remind you that
you need a throat to make jokes?

101
00:06:14,608 --> 00:06:15,632
Relax.

102
00:06:16,977 --> 00:06:18,775
You can close
your eyes if you like.

103
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:21,137
Stay still, Max.

104
00:06:29,422 --> 00:06:30,446
Done.

105
00:06:33,260 --> 00:06:34,319
I think it's fair to say

106
00:06:34,427 --> 00:06:35,725
that was torture for both of us.

107
00:06:37,564 --> 00:06:40,261
If my cancer gets anyone
else killed besides me,

108
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:42,131
then I'm really gonna be upset.

109
00:06:43,136 --> 00:06:44,399
I got the 911.

110
00:06:44,471 --> 00:06:47,839
This week's the annual conference of
cardiothoracic surgeons in San Diego.

111
00:06:47,941 --> 00:06:49,741
Everyone goes. All of
my attendings are there.

112
00:06:50,410 --> 00:06:52,936
One unlucky surgeon stays
behind at each hospital to cover.

113
00:06:53,013 --> 00:06:54,811
It's me here, it's
Fernandez at Baptist,

114
00:06:54,915 --> 00:06:57,111
but only one of us has a
dissecting aortic aneurysm.

115
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:00,013
And since he's here, I'm
guessing no one's covering Baptist.

116
00:07:00,287 --> 00:07:02,131
They still have general
surgeons, transplant surgeons.

117
00:07:02,155 --> 00:07:03,623
Yeah, they can't
cover for Fernandez.

118
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:06,159
You want a gynecologist
tagging in on your heart surgery?

119
00:07:09,362 --> 00:07:12,457
How can Baptist run their hospital
without a cardiothoracic surgeon?

120
00:07:12,532 --> 00:07:15,111
They can't. Which means they're
no longer a level-one trauma center.

121
00:07:15,135 --> 00:07:18,128
Without cardiothoracic backup,
they can't treat myocardial infarctions,

122
00:07:18,204 --> 00:07:20,764
car accidents, GSWs...
They can't accept ambulances.

123
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:23,185
Guys, we're gonna have to pick
up Baptist's full ambulance load.

124
00:07:23,209 --> 00:07:24,507
I knew you were gonna say that.

125
00:07:24,611 --> 00:07:25,688
They'd do it for us. Would they?

126
00:07:25,712 --> 00:07:27,957
We're short-staffed too. What
about their network hospitals?

127
00:07:27,981 --> 00:07:30,981
They'll pick up the elective admits,
but emergency patients will die waiting

128
00:07:31,017 --> 00:07:33,097
in cross-town traffic.
We're the closest. It's on us.

129
00:07:33,153 --> 00:07:34,314
You really think we can

130
00:07:34,387 --> 00:07:37,016
shoulder their full ED plus all
the cardiothoracic surgeries?

131
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,668
Just the ones that
need to be done today.

132
00:07:38,692 --> 00:07:39,716
Yeah, just those.

133
00:07:39,826 --> 00:07:40,850
Guys, this is what we do.

134
00:07:40,961 --> 00:07:42,156
We help everyone.

135
00:07:42,462 --> 00:07:45,796
Floyd, I trust you and I believe
in you, so I am only gonna do this

136
00:07:45,865 --> 00:07:47,299
if you tell me
you can handle it.

137
00:07:47,367 --> 00:07:48,960
I can handle it. Okay, good,

138
00:07:49,035 --> 00:07:51,147
because if something goes
wrong, we are both on the hook.

139
00:07:51,171 --> 00:07:53,970
Nothing will go wrong,
all right? I'll make sure of it.

140
00:07:56,409 --> 00:07:57,468
Okay.

141
00:08:04,417 --> 00:08:07,080
Bloom, we're gonna live or
die today based on our ED load.

142
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:10,490
So, any doc or nurse standing
still in any part of this hospital

143
00:08:10,557 --> 00:08:11,901
needs to go down and pitch in.

144
00:08:11,925 --> 00:08:13,826
I'll take it. I
already hear sirens,

145
00:08:13,893 --> 00:08:15,972
so unfortunately, you're gonna have
to miss the rest of my big pep talk.

146
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:17,020
Aw, so sad.

147
00:08:17,097 --> 00:08:18,929
Iggy, psych wait
times are the longest,

148
00:08:19,032 --> 00:08:21,672
so make sure you get your patients
up to your ward early and often.

149
00:08:21,701 --> 00:08:23,821
All right. Good thing psych
patients are so compliant.

150
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:27,149
Kapoor, neurology wait times are second,
so I need you to move double time today.

151
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,267
This is my double time. Noted.

152
00:08:29,376 --> 00:08:31,368
Sharpe. This is a bad idea.

153
00:08:31,444 --> 00:08:33,389
So is sending every
cardiothoracic surgeon in America

154
00:08:33,413 --> 00:08:34,523
to San Diego at the same time,

155
00:08:34,547 --> 00:08:36,175
but they do it every year.

156
00:08:36,249 --> 00:08:38,582
Last year was Barcelona.
I do love sangria.

157
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:40,381
This is a bad idea.
So, are you telling me

158
00:08:40,453 --> 00:08:42,198
that you wouldn't have
taken the extra patients?

159
00:08:42,222 --> 00:08:43,520
No, I wouldn't have.

160
00:08:43,590 --> 00:08:45,786
I try to make
things simple, easy.

161
00:08:46,059 --> 00:08:47,960
You know, like a
normal person. Ah.

162
00:08:48,228 --> 00:08:51,289
Why do you keep choosing the
hardest road at every opportunity?

163
00:08:52,132 --> 00:08:53,191
Better views?

164
00:08:58,905 --> 00:09:00,965
Tall person, how long have
you been with Reynolds?

165
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:03,908
Three years. And
it's Nottingham.

166
00:09:03,977 --> 00:09:06,276
I'm a PGY-6, so...
Okay, today is not the day

167
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:08,339
where I'm gonna be polite
and remember your names.

168
00:09:08,715 --> 00:09:10,775
When patients come in,
I'm gonna point and yell.

169
00:09:10,984 --> 00:09:13,647
Don't take it personally.
You move on my orders only.

170
00:09:22,429 --> 00:09:24,261
What'd you bring
us? Adaline Simon.

171
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:26,799
53-year-old female, had a
pleurodesis on the books at Baptist.

172
00:09:27,100 --> 00:09:31,299
Tall person, take Mrs. Simon to any
empty bed and get her prepped for surgery.

173
00:09:31,504 --> 00:09:34,269
This is Mr. Gold, 47-year-old
male in need of a VATS procedure.

174
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:36,969
Casey and brown-haired
woman. Any open bay.

175
00:09:37,077 --> 00:09:38,797
Name is Sherry Fletcher.
68-year-old female.

176
00:09:38,845 --> 00:09:40,085
She requires a mediastinoscopy.

177
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:43,006
Stay with me. Okay,
let's get her inside.

178
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:47,847
Okay, put Mrs.
Fletcher in bay 23.

179
00:09:49,489 --> 00:09:51,185
Has anybody seen my ibuprofen?

180
00:09:51,291 --> 00:09:52,968
Tell a nurse to grab
you a bottle from the...

