this is the scariest
day of their lives.

308
00:16:47,573 --> 00:16:50,319
They woke up needing major surgery,
then they were thrown into an ambulance

309
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:52,488
and dragged across town so
that a doctor they don't know

310
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:53,775
can cut open their hearts.

311
00:16:53,946 --> 00:16:56,438
They're trusting me, just
like Max is trusting me.

312
00:16:56,549 --> 00:16:58,160
And I'm not putting
that kind of pressure on

313
00:16:58,184 --> 00:16:59,995
a first-year resident
straight out of med school.

314
00:17:00,019 --> 00:17:01,459
Oh, we got a bleeder.

315
00:17:01,754 --> 00:17:03,586
Are the patients
downstairs stable?

316
00:17:03,689 --> 00:17:05,419
Yeah. Then they can wait.

317
00:17:05,892 --> 00:17:08,437
I am giving you one hour and then I
am sending them somewhere else.

318
00:17:08,461 --> 00:17:09,621
All right, here we go.

319
00:17:11,364 --> 00:17:12,457
Suction.

320
00:17:13,266 --> 00:17:16,395
Mrs. Monaghan, can you
describe your symptoms now?

321
00:17:17,103 --> 00:17:18,594
Dizzy!

322
00:17:20,907 --> 00:17:22,273
Are you even a real doctor?

323
00:17:22,542 --> 00:17:24,204
Yes, and I'm trying to help you.

324
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:27,309
Good, then give me something
for dizzy so I can go home.

325
00:17:27,613 --> 00:17:30,447
I would love to do that, but I want
to give you the right something.

326
00:17:33,719 --> 00:17:35,551
I'll give you more time. You...

327
00:17:37,456 --> 00:17:38,890
She's gonna be here all day.

328
00:17:38,958 --> 00:17:43,623
Maybe, but fast and wrong is not
a service to her or to anyone else.

329
00:17:49,602 --> 00:17:51,969
Dr. Bloom? What
are you looking for?

330
00:17:52,939 --> 00:17:55,067
Are you, uh, getting
her out of my ED?

331
00:17:55,908 --> 00:17:57,001
Not as yet.

332
00:17:57,476 --> 00:18:00,156
Can you get some other patients
out of here? Something's gotta give.

333
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:03,576
Oh, and you should
totally give Ella your pastry.

334
00:18:04,951 --> 00:18:07,147
So, you do understand it
was a harmless gesture.

335
00:18:07,253 --> 00:18:08,533
Oh, I think it's a huge mistake,

336
00:18:08,588 --> 00:18:09,748
but I want to see you suffer.

337
00:18:12,124 --> 00:18:13,786
Oh!

338
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:15,360
Laddus are not pastries!

339
00:18:16,696 --> 00:18:18,289
It's like my
college sit-in days.

340
00:18:18,364 --> 00:18:20,924
Every chair occupied, so
people just lie on the floor.

341
00:18:22,168 --> 00:18:25,002
Almost on tilt and
four hours to go.

342
00:18:27,707 --> 00:18:29,300
Go steal the chemo
chairs from onc.

343
00:18:29,709 --> 00:18:30,768
Oh.

344
00:18:30,843 --> 00:18:34,837
Grab and go. Also like
my college days. On it.

345
00:18:44,490 --> 00:18:47,187
Jemma. Jemma, wait. Hey.
Whoa, whoa. Are you okay?

346
00:18:47,293 --> 00:18:49,694
No, I'm not okay.
None of this is okay.

347
00:18:49,795 --> 00:18:51,889
Jemma, hang on. We're
trying our best here.

348
00:18:52,198 --> 00:18:53,564
Okay? It's an uphill battle.

349
00:18:53,866 --> 00:18:54,890
What?

350
00:18:55,368 --> 00:18:56,728
What's this? What's
happening here?

351
00:18:56,802 --> 00:18:58,168
Transfers from the ED.

352
00:18:58,237 --> 00:19:00,331
No, no. Uh-uh. No. No vacancies.

353
00:19:00,406 --> 00:19:01,897
We're all full up. So is the ED.

354
00:19:02,074 --> 00:19:03,235
I'm not their safety valve.

355
00:19:03,576 --> 00:19:04,805
All right, let's go. I just...

356
00:19:05,011 --> 00:19:06,877
Yeah, come in.

357
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:09,312
This is exactly why we
needed the community garden.

358
00:19:09,749 --> 00:19:12,048
What happened to the
garden? I have to kill it.

359
00:19:12,218 --> 00:19:14,210
You have been wanting
that garden for years.

360
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:16,585
Yeah, just not with
Volt Cola attached.

361
00:19:17,089 --> 00:19:20,218
In India, Volt Cola builds
playgrounds, football fields,

362
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:21,919
cricket pitches
for kids to play on.

363
00:19:22,028 --> 00:19:23,929
Which means land,
which takes money.

364
00:19:24,030 --> 00:19:26,226
Would a garden make a
difference to these kids too?

365
00:19:26,932 --> 00:19:27,991
Yeah.

366
00:19:30,069 --> 00:19:31,594
Yeah, it would.

367
00:19:39,945 --> 00:19:41,573
Tianna's cancer's back.

368
00:19:44,950 --> 00:19:46,441
Ewing's sarcoma.

369
00:19:48,054 --> 00:19:49,716
It's extremely aggressive.

370
00:19:52,224 --> 00:19:53,522
I'm very sorry.

371
00:19:59,265 --> 00:20:01,757
What about something
experimental?

372
00:20:03,269 --> 00:20:06,637
Unfortunately, there are no
clinical trials for kids her age.

373
00:20:06,906 --> 00:20:08,966
There has to be
more out there. Uh...

374
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:10,899
Other countries.

375
00:20:11,477 --> 00:20:13,105
Um...

376
00:20:13,212 --> 00:20:14,737
There has to be something else.

377
00:20:19,418 --> 00:20:20,613
I think

378
00:20:22,555 --> 00:20:26,492
that we should discuss
palliative care options.

379
00:20:31,430 --> 00:20:34,662
How do we tell her? We don't.

380
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,263
We can't.

381
00:20:38,270 --> 00:20:40,068
Tianna is smart.

382
00:20:40,806 --> 00:20:44,106
She is asking questions.
She is looking for answers.

383
00:20:45,845 --> 00:20:48,781
The best course
of... I can't tell her.

384
00:20:53,686 --> 00:20:54,745
Can you?

385
00:21:07,166 --> 00:21:08,777
Who are you? What'd
you bring this guy here for?

386
00:21:08,801 --> 00:21:10,633
He's a doctor and
his name is Max.

387
00:21:10,870 --> 00:21:12,202
You brought a
doctor to our house?

388
00:21:12,304 --> 00:21:13,602
Hey, hey, hey. He can help.

389
00:21:13,672 --> 00:21:14,912
We don't need his kind of help.

390
00:21:15,207 --> 00:21:16,766
Give him a chance, Paul.

391
00:21:23,149 --> 00:21:24,173
Just...

392
00:21:25,718 --> 00:21:26,777
It's okay.

393
00:21:37,696 --> 00:21:38,891
Where are you from?

394
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:42,529
Are you from the Midwest?

395
00:21:42,635 --> 00:21:45,469
Hamilton, Ohio. Born and raised.

396
00:21:45,871 --> 00:21:46,895
Why?

397
00:21:50,876 --> 00:21:52,572
Vance, you may
have a fungal infection,

398
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:54,738
and if it's the kind
that I think it is,

399
00:21:55,581 --> 00:21:57,359
we need to get you into
New Amsterdam right now.

400
00:21:57,383 --> 00:22:00,376
No, man. No hospital.

401
00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:02,330
All right, what you got to do
now is just get the hell out of here.

402
00:22:02,354 --> 00:22:03,965
I don't know what you
have against hospitals,

403
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:06,754
but if we don't take your brother
to New Amsterdam right now,

404
00:22:06,859 --> 00:22:07,883
he is going to die.

405
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:10,656
That's exactly what the other
doctors said when Mom was sick.

406
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:14,057
Except rather than help,
they just kept bringing bills.

407
00:22:14,433 --> 00:22:15,901
We lost our apartment.

408
00:22:16,001 --> 00:22:17,993
The debt collectors
took the rest.

409
00:22:20,239 --> 00:22:23,732
I promise you will never see a
single bill from New Amsterdam.

410
00:22:25,211 --> 00:22:26,509
What do you say, Vance?

411
00:22:27,746 --> 00:22:30,716
I took a gamble on you coming
here, leaving my own hospital.

412
00:22:31,884 --> 00:22:33,164
You want to take a gamble on me?

413
00:22:37,356 --> 00:22:38,585
Go away, man.

414
00:22:40,926 --> 00:22:42,087
You heard him.

415
00:22:43,462 --> 00:22:44,521
Get out of here.

416
00:23:05,284 --> 00:23:07,446
The graft's pulling
taut. It's too damn small.

417
00:23:14,927 --> 00:23:16,088
What?

418
00:23:16,161 --> 00:23:18,001
Everyone is prepped,
so I thought I'd scrub in.

419
00:23:18,063 --> 00:23:19,087
No.

420
00:23:19,598 --> 00:23:21,624
I've watched you do
this surgery four times.

421
00:23:21,734 --> 00:23:23,812
I know to ligate the internal mammary
before transecting the intercostal.

422
00:23:23,836 --> 00:23:24,895
I know...

423
00:23:25,004 --> 00:23:27,599
I don't need you in here.
I need you out there.

424
00:23:27,806 --> 00:23:28,830
Go!

425
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:31,102
Suture.

426
00:23:32,311 --> 00:23:33,335
Suture.

427
00:23:42,288 --> 00:23:43,415
Excuse me.

428
00:23:43,622 --> 00:23:45,818
Excuse me! That is my chair!

429
00:23:51,630 --> 00:23:52,654
I said I ain't moving.

430
00:23:53,032 --> 00:23:54,792
You're not the only
dumbass that needs space!

431
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:59,298
Fight, fight, fight!

432
00:23:59,371 --> 00:24:02,273
Thanks. Over there. Not now.

433
00:24:08,213 --> 00:24:10,307
Goodwin! Where the
hell have you been?

434
00:24:10,983 --> 00:24:12,383
It's like a damn
MASH unit in here.

435
00:24:12,685 --> 00:24:14,551
Dean, I had to take...
What were you thinking?

436
00:24:14,853 --> 00:24:18,620
Bloom, get all the department
heads down here. Now.

437
00:24:20,392 --> 00:24:22,054
Here you go, Doctor.

438
00:24:27,032 --> 00:24:30,332
Okay, I'll make
this quick and clear.

439
00:24:30,736 --> 00:24:34,195
I screwed up. All
this chaos, it's on me.

440
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:36,426
I overcommitted us and
then went out looking for more.

441
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:39,636
I thought I could help everyone
and ended up helping no one.

442
00:24:39,845 --> 00:24:41,725
I'm not asking for
understanding or forgiveness,

443
00:24:41,914 --> 00:24:44,679
but I am asking you
to help me fix this.

444
00:24:45,084 --> 00:24:47,383
So, here's the plan.

445
00:24:47,486 --> 00:24:49,978
Reynolds, I am sorry that I
put so much pressure on you.

446
00:24:50,055 --> 00:24:51,318
How can I take some of it off?

447
00:24:51,390 --> 00:24:53,590
Are any of the surgeries
waiting in the ED stable enough

448
00:24:53,726 --> 00:24:54,750
<i>to go to Mount Zion?</i> Two.

449
00:24:54,860 --> 00:24:57,056
I'll send them. Bloom,
anywhere there's an open bed,

450
00:24:57,162 --> 00:24:59,063
admit a patient to it.
Admit everyone you can.

451
00:24:59,198 --> 00:25:01,599
And what if we don't get
reimbursed for the beds?

452
00:25:01,700 --> 00:25:03,362
I'll send Baptist
the bill. Iggy.

453
00:25:03,569 --> 00:25:05,663
Captain? Take your
patients to the cafeteria,

454
00:25:05,738 --> 00:25:08,902
to the roof, for a walk. Anywhere to
keep them busy and out of the ward.

455
00:25:09,274 --> 00:25:10,537
Aye-aye. Sharpe.

456
00:25:10,609 --> 00:25:13,238
I know what I have to
do. Great. Any questions?

457
00:25:15,214 --> 00:25:18,378
Any questions not about
Kapoor's laddu situation?

458
00:25:18,784 --> 00:25:19,843
No. Go.

459
00:25:25,024 --> 00:25:28,859
Max, I don't know how
you're gonna pull this off.

460
00:25:29,228 --> 00:25:31,629
We are all gonna work together.

461
00:25:32,364 --> 00:25:33,423
Including you.

462
00:25:33,766 --> 00:25:36,565
I could really use
your help, Dr. Fulton.

463
00:25:43,642 --> 00:25:47,204
The flat metal part goes
on the patient's chest.

464
00:26:02,494 --> 00:26:03,757
How are you holding up?

465
00:26:05,664 --> 00:26:08,600
I thought getting the news
would be the hard part,

466
00:26:10,469 --> 00:26:12,802
but telling Tianna's a
million times harder.

467
00:26:17,609 --> 00:26:18,838
You shouldn't have to.

468
00:26:19,978 --> 00:26:21,276
You be her mum.

469
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:24,106
I'll be her doctor.

470
00:26:26,518 --> 00:26:27,611
I'll tell her.

471
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,160
In for a little treat here.

472
00:26:36,695 --> 00:26:37,788
Come on. Come on out.

473
00:26:39,932 --> 00:26:40,956
Okay.

474
00:26:41,700 --> 00:26:45,967
So, it's not a garden, but, uh, you
know, it's outside. It's fresh-air therapy.

475
00:26:46,438 --> 00:26:48,998
We got a wonderful view
of the city, so, you know,

476
00:26:49,875 --> 00:26:52,777
spread out, feel the space.
Find your own spot, all right?

477
00:26:55,347 --> 00:26:58,146
Jemma, hi. What's
going on? Talk to me.

478
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:00,712
There's nothing to say.

479
00:27:01,787 --> 00:27:05,349
Well, I heard that Blanca's
background check came through clean.

480
00:27:06,125 --> 00:27:07,320
That's good news, right?

481
00:27:09,394 --> 00:27:10,862
Yeah. Yeah.

482
00:27:14,032 --> 00:27:16,194
But, like, the site visit
keeps getting pushed back.

483
00:27:16,702 --> 00:27:19,536
It isn't for months. And
there's, like, 100 other things

